Tropical Storm Katia Will Probably Become Hurricane Later Today, U.S. Says

-- B y   C h a r l o t t e   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-08-31T14:42:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/tropical-storm-katia-will-probably-become-hurricane-later-today-u-s-says.html
Tropical Storm Katia, its winds
still 65 miles (105 kilometers) an hour, probably will reach
hurricane strength later today, the U.S. National Hurricane
Center said in an advisory at about 10:40 a.m. East Coast time.  Katia is 1,100 miles west of the southernmost Cape Verde
Islands and moving west-northwest at 21 mph, the center said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charlotte Porter at 
 cporter11@bloomberg.net  